EmailTemplate.subject: Live Different DR/Haiti Build
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hi {!Contact.FirstName},
Thank you for registering for a Live Different Build!
We're so glad that you're joining us for this unique trip that is taking place in both the Dominican Republic and Haiti.
Please review the following information to help you prepare for your trip:
Your Deposit is Due in Two Weeks:
Your first $300 deposit needs to be made within 2 weeks of your registration to secure your spot on the trip. Use your Canada Helps Page for making, entering and requesting donations or payments related to your trip. You can share (email, Facebook, etc.) your Canada Helps Page with any potential donors so they can donate online to your Live Different Builds project. For instructions on how to create a Canada Helps page: http://livedifferent.com/builds/alumni-build-2016-haitidr#canadahelps
Forms Attached to this Email:
Consent Forms - Please scan and email these forms back to me within 2 weeks of registration. Please note that we need a new consent form for every trip you come on. Child Protection Policy - The Child Protection Policy is for volunteers 18 years of age or older to read before the trip. It is our policy on what is appropriate behaviour when dealing with minors and the steps that we take to protect them. It's important that you take the time to read this from beginning to end. Child Protection Policy Agreement - Once you have read the above Child Protection Policy, please sign the agreement and send it to me. This can also be scanned and emailed, or faxed to me as we do not need the original copy. Letter to Donors - This a great tool for fund raising. Present this letter to potential donors and businesses when looking for donations towards your trip. It gives an explanation of who Live Different is and what Live Different Builds is all about. It's also a good idea to include a letter from yourself explaining why you want to participate on a Live Different Build and what you hope to accomplish. Packing List - No idea what to pack? Read this list and it will remind you of all the little things that will make your trip and travels more comfortable.
Criminal Record Check - If you will be 18 years of age on the trip, you will be required to obtain a criminal record check. You can obtain one through your local police station, or ask me how to do it online. - Note: If you have already provided us with a Criminal Record Check, and it is no more than 2 years old, you will not need to provide us with a new one.
Booking your flights:
Airport: Puerto Plata, Dominican Republic - Airport Code: POP Arrival: July 18, 2016 Departure: July 31, 2016
Official Airline of Live Different: WestJet! WestJet has given Live Different volunteers a way to save up to 10% on flights. Call the WestJet Groups Department at 1-888-493-7853 and give them the convention code: CC7946.
Airport Shuttle: - Once you have booked your flights, please forward me your flight itinerary. - When you arrive at the Puerto Plata Airport, our staff will be at the gate wearing a Live Different t-shirt and holding a Live Different sign. You will then be taken to Sosua by the Sea Resort in Sosua (10 minutes away from the airport).
Accommodations: - While in the Dominican Republic: We stay at a small and clean resort called Sosua by the Sea. It is located 10 minutes away from the Puerto Plata Airport in a town called Sosua. - While in Haiti: We stay at a resort called Royal Residence. It is located 10 minutes away from where we build our school in a small town called Calvaire in the city of Cap Haitien. - The rooms provided at both accommodations can fit up to 4 people in a room with 2-3 beds. There is a private pool (DR and HT) and beach (DR only) that is accessible for all volunteers. - There is a buffet-style dining hall that we are able to transform into an event hall for all of our evening activities. The hotel has security guards that monitor the resort at all times to ensure our safety. - Shower towels, beach towels, a safe with a key, and bedding are all provided by the resort.
Transportation: We hire bus drivers for transportation and they arrive every morning at the resort to take us to the communities we will be working in. The drivers are experienced drivers whom we have been working with since 2005. They have experience driving in Dominican Republic and Haiti, as well as the legal documents to drive these registered vehicles.
Communities We Work In: Since 2010, we have developed very strong relationships with the community of Calvaire that we work in. The community knows Live Different very well and we feel very safe at all times while working on our building sites.
Work Site Safety: We require all volunteers to bring closed toed shoes, a hat/bandana, waterbottle, sunglasses, sunscreen, and leather work gloves. This ensures that volunteers are as equipped for handling equipment on the job sites.
Vaccinations and Medications: We do not require that any of our volunteers receive any vaccinations or medications to go to any of the countries that we work in. But, we do suggest that every volunteer visit their family doctor or local medical clinic and decide on your own about taking any medications or vaccinations prior to the trip.
Contact during a trip between volunteers and Canada: - There is wifi available at the resort and a wifi code can be purchased at the front desk. - Due to the fact that we will be using internet in a developing country, it will be hard for volunteers to receive a well enough connection to skype with their family members, but they can indeed use Facebook and e-mail. - All of our staff have cell phones on them at all times. We will be emailing everyone all of the emergency contact information before the trip starts.
DR/Haiti Build 2016 Trip Page: Visit this link to view your trip page. Here you can read your trip itinerary and find information on how to create a Canada Helps page. It will also be updated with project details once they become available. http://livedifferent.com/builds/haiti-dominican-public-build
Photos and Videos: Here are some photos and videos from our past Live Different Builds if you would like to use them for your fundraising needs: https://www.dropbox.com/sh/3wke2n7mm37rg7e/E0VsZOT3q8
Check out our Live Different Facebook Page!: There are photos, blogs and videos from our most recent trips, it's a great resource to help you prepare for your trip: http://www.facebook.com/pages/Live-Different/189864944417296.
Visit our FAQ Section: You can also visit our FAQ section on our website as it is a great resource. http://www.livedifferent.com/faqs
Thank you for taking the time to read the above information. If you have any questions at all, please don't hesitate to contact me. I'm always here to help!
Sincerely,
Joy Yu Program Administrator
